with clang. It's a lot longer with gcc! Tested against Boost 1.63 and 1.64 with pybind11 master.

The same code does work against mapbox/variant.

`boost::variable` is super useful and it will be a while before many projects can use `std::variant`, so it might be and idea to add a Boost version to the tests.

## Problem Definition

Using just a array of participants results in some cumbersome address handling.

## Solution

Provide a mapping from participant address to array index.

## Example

Instead of:

```
        Participant storage participant = self.participants[0];
        if (participant.node_address != caller_address) {
            participant = self.participants[1];
            if (participant.node_address != caller_address) {
                throw;
            }
        }
```

Use a simpler approach like:
```
  uint index = index_or_throw(called_address);
  Participant storage participant = self.participants[index];
```

Due to [security reasons](https://cryptocoding.net/index.php/Coding_rules#Compare_secret_strings_in_constant_time) `constant_time_compare` should be used to compare the two `state` parameters within the `validate_state` method instead of the `==` in the `OAuthAuth ` class ([here](https://github.com/python-social-auth/social-core/blob/master/social_core/backends/oauth.py#L90)).

`constant_time_compare` is available in the [`social-core/utils.py`](https://github.com/python-social-auth/social-core/blob/master/social_core/utils.py#L213).

```
elif not state:
    raise AuthStateMissing(self, 'state')
elif not constant_time_compare(request_state,state):
    raise AuthStateForbidden(self)
else:
    return state
```
